## Artifact durability (apply to every action)

The artifacts an action references must be durable in the Git-tracked repository. Accept any of: a prior commit referenced by the action, attachments on this entry (`--attach`), or attachments on a referenced upstream entry already in the graph.

- `high` — Action claims work was done but references no durable artifact (no commit, no attachment, no upstream attachment). The action description alone is not evidence of durability.
- `low` — Durable artifacts exist but the action doesn't explicitly name them (e.g. describes changes without citing the commit or attachment).
- No finding — Action references a commit, carries an attachment, or references an upstream entry that has the relevant attachment.
